PROTECT VERMOUTH FROM AIR
Hints
It's actually a delieate, fragile vrine.
Keep cool, tightly corked.
for the Home Bar
KEEP GLASSWARE RIGHT SIDE UP
Otherwise soap fumen,
which are liabbe to be retained after washing,
may easily ruin a drink's flavor.
CORRECT MEASUREMENT
Have a jigger (1% az.) or a measering glass on hand.
A dash is equal to seven or eight drops.
The quantities mentioned in the recipes
refer to one drink
MIXING INGREDIENTS
To insure satisfaetion, follow recipes exactly.
ALWAYS REMEMBER:
except ubere otherwite specified.
Frem them you ean easily caleulate the amounts
to use for mixing any mumber of drinks.
A mixed drink in never better
than the liquor brand used. So chocse it with eare
-there is no sabatitute for quality!
TYPE OF SUGAR
Alrays use fine granulated sugar to avoid caking
and to assure thorough dilution.
Do not use eonfeetiner' nugar.
ICE IN COCKTAILS
Do not allow a shakerful to stand too long with ice-
for drinks go flat from execssive dilution.
WHEN TO SHAKE
Shake all cocktails that contain fruit julees.
Others should be stirred.
PREPARING FRUITS
Be sure to slice or seneese fruit just prior to use.
If left to stand, fruit and fruit juices go stale,
even under refrigeration.
SERVE DRINKS ICE-COLD
Some hosts precool both liquor and glassware.
It'sa good practice.
